<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Prothallus not seen. Thallus white, endolithic. Perithecia 0.11-0.36 mm, immersed, leaving deep pits in the rock. Involucrellum absent. Exciple ca. 0.25 mm in diam., wall dark. Periphysoids ca. 25-35 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, sparsely branching, 
<taxonomicName class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Bagliettoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bagliettoa" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Bagliettoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like. Ascospores 0-septate (only few seen), 15-18 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-8 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
According to the protologue (
<bibRefCitation author="Servit, M" journalOrPublisher="Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="67 - 115" refId="B48" refString="Servit, M, 1948. The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II. Studia Botanica Cechoslovaca 9: 67 - 115" title="The new lichens of the Pyrenocarpae-group. II." volume="9" year="1948">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Servít">Servit</normalizedToken>
1948
</bibRefCitation>
), the spore size is 20-28 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-8 mm. The species may be related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gueidan &amp; Cl. Roux" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="DC." class="Eurotiomycetes" family="Verrucariaceae" genus="Bagliettoa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bagliettoa calciseda" order="Verrucariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="calciseda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Bagliettoa calciseda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(DC.) Gueidan &amp; Cl. Roux.
</paragraph>
